</ul>
<h3 id="toc15"><span>Week of April 22nd:</span></h3>
<h4 id="toc16"><span>SCPs</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3594">SCP-3594</a> (&quot;Genesis Ulcer&quot;) - <em>&quot; SCP-3594 is an entity that claims to be a wart located on the back of an adult male Ceratophrys, henceforth designated as SCP-3594-A.&quot;</em> Written by whomstdveWorm.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3363">SCP-3363</a> (&quot;The Citizen Kane of Lightning-induced Reality TV&quot;) - A Thousand Ways to Die Special: Featuring YOU! Written by Mortos.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3716">SCP-3716</a> (&quot;Boned Beyond Belief&quot;) - The power to deglove my entire body is not a power I want at all. Written by MaliceAforethought.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-1094-ex">SCP-1094-EX</a> (&quot;Playground of the Lost&quot;) - Space has its eye on us. Written by MrBazzle.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3893">SCP-3893</a> (&quot;I'm Going to Have a Motherfucking Meltdown&quot;) - As it turns out, using a radioactive human as a nuclear fuel source isn't the best of ideas. Written by CadaverCommander.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3573">SCP-3573</a> (&quot;The Rubedo Reserve Oinopoeic Sublimator&quot;) - The Alagaddan champaign has always been celebrated for its excellence. Written by ch00bakka.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3815">SCP-3815</a> (&quot;Elena the Ever-Present&quot;) - <em>&quot;SCP-3815 is an entity whose immediate location is solely dependent upon being in the sightline of the nearest human being, disregarding itself.&quot;</em> Written by DrRosencrantz.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3881">SCP-3881</a> (&quot;A Disregarded Proposal&quot;) - &quot;Not a 001&quot; Written by Dr Aers.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3589">SCP-3589</a> (&quot;Second Amendment&quot;) - Better keep this one at arm's length. Written by Weryllium.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3696">SCP-3696</a> (&quot;The Greatest Attractor&quot;) - <em>&quot;Measurements taken of SCP-3696 suggest that it is a highly localized concentration of mass many thousands of times more massive than the Milky Way galaxy.&quot;</em> Written by Doctor Cullmann.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3708">SCP-3708</a> (&quot;Crows Unanswered&quot;) - Waiting for a response which will never be. Written by Dr Vaughn.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3353">SCP-3353</a> (&quot;Secrets for Sweets&quot;) - The truth is sweeter than pastries, but nearly as tasty. Written by Zyn.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3767">SCP-3767</a> (&quot;Additional Baggage Fee&quot;) - <em>&quot;Once the sky has changed colors entirely, the plane stops all translational movement, and enters a slowed free fall. &quot;</em> Written by Captain Kirby.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3498">SCP-3498</a> (&quot;Brebauenitis&quot;) - <em>&quot;SCP-3498 will begin to transform internal organs into miniaturized structures of Ptolemaic Egyptian architecture.&quot;</em> Written by Moenennbys.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3292">SCP-3292</a> (&quot;The Land Before Time, For All of Time&quot;) - A record of the before times, left untouched by modern evils. Written by whomstdveWorm.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3328">SCP-3328</a> (&quot;Where Dead Men Grow&quot;) - The thing which lies just beyond the trenches. Written by Blibby_Blobfish.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-2235">URA-9611</a> (&quot;The Ozymandias Effect&quot;) - Look upon my works, ye mighty, and despair. Written by MaliceAforethought.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3840">SCP-3840</a> (&quot;We Stand On Guard For Thee&quot;) - <em>&quot;Mercier begins profusely coughing and gasping for air until a burnt phone battery is ejected from their mouth, which collides with the ceiling and lands on the table.&quot;</em> Written by 9Volt.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3157">SCP-3157</a> (&quot;The Second Castle&quot;) - The ride never ends. Written by Whitecastle.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3239">SCP-3239</a> (&quot;When Death Comes Calling&quot;) - You can't but help to pick up. Written by The Shrimp.</li>
<li><a href="/scp-3693">SCP-3693</a> (&quot;Postscript - Through A Glass, Darkly&quot;) - <em>&quot;SCP-3693 can only be seen by observers when their eyes are closed.&quot;</em> Written by djkaktus and The Great Hippo</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc17"><span>Tales</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/programmed-to-receive">Programmed to Receive</a> - <em>&quot;&quot;So, what, you've got a whole fleet of Roombas?&quot; Janice asked sarcastically.&quot;</em> Written by Jim North.</li>
<li><a href="/end-of-line">End of Line</a> - <em>&quot;A spectral Taita unit was in hot pursuit, its numerous legs crawling after her.&quot;</em> Written by Jacob Conwell.</li>
<li><a href="/consent-form-3436-a">Consent Form 3436-A</a> - <em>&quot;They could only tell me one thing; Jim was someone to be very proud of.&quot;</em> Written by scpcrnp.</li>
<li><a href="/mobile-task-furries">Mobile Task Furries</a> - <em>&quot;It's twelve A.M., and we're the guys they called to take down an anomalous furry.&quot;</em> Written by Dog Teeth.</li>
<li><a href="/erasure">Do You Wish You Could Disappear?</a> - The Foundation can do anything to ensure continued containment. The Foundation will do anything to ensure continued containment. Written by Cyantreuse.</li>
<li><a href="/gordun-the-consumer">Gor'dun the Consumer</a> - <em>&quot;The alien, clinical words brought a rare gaze of bewilderment forth from Gor'dun the Consumer as he watched the messenger depart his throne room.&quot;</em> Written by kingpogan.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc18"><span>GOI Formats</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/squid-ispolin">GRU-P casefile &quot;SQUID ISPOLIN&quot;</a> - [GRU-P] <em>&quot;If the Americans were forced to deploy a nuclear weapon against themselves, it would be truly devastating for morale, and would not be easily traced back to the Soviet Union.&quot;</em> Written by stormbreath.</li>
<li><a href="/snitchdungeons">Carroll #332: The Snitch Dungeons</a> - [Chicago Spirit] <em>&quot;In 1930, we had a snitch problem.&quot;</em> Written by ObserverSeptember.</li>
<li><a href="/spc-2922">SPC-2922</a> - [SPC] <em>&quot;SPC-2922 consists of a single component: Marine Fighting Team ARMÁ ORÚN, an army-sized battalion comprised of nearly every deceased individual who professed loyalty to the Centre prior to their deaths.&quot;</em> Written by stormbreath.</li>
</ul>
