<h4 id="toc21"><span>Fancontent!</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/lostandfoundation">Lost and Foundation Hub</a> - A collection of podcasts critiquing random articles, organized by Communism will win! Go check it out!</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kozd6JVjXuo&amp;t=1s+here">SCP-2864: Di Molte Voci (Featuring 11 SCP Readers!)</a> A reading of <a href="/scp-2864">SCP-2864</a>, done by 11 SCP readers, organized by theesherm!</li>
<li><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCP/comments/8anxup/scp40jp_%E3%81%AD%E3%81%93%E3%81%A7%E3%81%99%E3%82%88%E3%82%8D%E3%81%97%E3%81%8F%E3%81%8A%E3%81%AD%E3%81%8C%E3%81%84%E3%81%97%E3%81%BE%E3%81%99_lego_moc/">SCP-40-JP (Lego MOC)</a> - A lego MOC of SCP-40-JP was made by none other than cephalopodstevenson! You can check out more of their stuff <a href="/cephalopodstevenson-artwork">here</a>!</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ypj1aUXG9-M">SCP Reading: So You Can Live In The Light</a> - An SCP reading of the tale <a href="/we-die-in-the-dark">So You Can Live in the Light</a> by the wonderful Doctor Cimmerian!</li>
<li><a href="http://amamy992.tumblr.com/post/173060410872/this-is-how-i-spend-end-of-the-world-april-9th">This is how I spend end of the world.</a> - A breathtaking piece of <a href="/scp-049">SCP-049</a> by <a href="http://amamy992.tumblr.com">Amamidori</a>!</li>
<li><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/SCP/comments/8cs1fj/remake_on_miniscp_2006_too_spooky/">Remake on mini-scp 2006, &quot;too spooky&quot;</a> - A wonderful paper art of <a href="/scp-2006">SCP-2006</a> by reddit user <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/PLAGUE_DOKTOR">PLAGUE_DOKTOR</a>!</li>
<li>windycat made three pieces in April; <a href="http://failcatsfailart.tumblr.com/post/173126480425/harrison-harrison-and-harrison-because-there-are">Harrison</a>, <a href="http://failcatsfailart.tumblr.com/post/173091848370/i-remembered-that-05eve-is-african-so-i-fixed-my">an O5</a>, and <a href="http://failcatsfailart.tumblr.com/post/172924727540/my-favourite-day-of-the-year-is-that-day-in-the">SCP-073</a>! Go check them out, and if you like what you see, you can find more on their <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-3848381#post-3796327">art thread</a>!</li>
</ul>
